The '''Select Bipartisan Committee to Investigate the Preparation for and Response to Hurricane Katrina''' was the [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]]' [[United States Congressional committee|congressional committee]] investigating the [[United States Government]]'s failure to respond appropriately to [[Hurricane Katrina]].
The committee was directed to cease 30&nbsp;days after releasing its final report. That report was released February 15, 2006.
==Members== Despite the committee's name, it actually did not operate on a bipartisan basis. The committee was to have 20 members, with 11 members from the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican majority]] and 9 members from the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic minority]]. However, Democrats did not to appoint any members to the committee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wikileaks.org/leak/crs/RS21243.pdf|title=Ad Hoc Select Committees: Use in the House of Representatives|last=Schneider|first=Judy|date=February 21, 2006|publisher=Congressional Research Service|accessdate=2009-02-12}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>
